        <section id="history">
            <h2>History of Cricket</h2>
            <p>Cricket originated in southeast England in the middle of the 16th century. By the end of the 18th century, it had developed into the national sport of England.</p>
            <blockquote>The game of cricket has a known history spanning from the 16th century to the present day, with international matches having been played since 1844.</blockquote>
        </section>
        <section id="rules">
            <h2>Basic Rules of Cricket</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Two teams of eleven players each.</li>
                <li>The game is played on a circular or oval-shaped field.</li>
                <li>The main objective is to score more runs than the opposing team.</li>
                <li>Runs are scored by hitting the ball and running between the wickets or by hitting boundaries.</li>
                <li>The game is divided into innings where one team bats and the other bowls and fields.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
